Program: The Documentary
Title: Vicky Phelan: The Woman who Changed Ireland
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/w3csy2q0
Last Broadcast Date: Sun 9 Dec 2018
This is the story of Vicky Phelan, a mother of two from Limerick, Ireland. Vicky has cancer of the cervix and in 2017 she was given just six months to live. As she battled to save her own life, Vicky uncovered a scandal that rocked the Irish establishment and exposed a country still coming to grips with radical social upheaval. As part of the ‘BBC 100 Women’ season, Helen Devlin meets the woman who changed Ireland. (Photo: Vicky Phelan. Credit: BBC) Show less